page.title: 13A day in my life
page.content: My day starts at quarter to seven in the morning.I get my dressing gown and slippers on and go downstairs to do some piano practice till quarter past seven,then I have my breakfast then I go upstairs and wake everyone else up.I then get washed, dressed and I clean my teeth.At twenty to eight My Mum takes my brother and I to school. At nine a.m. a whistle is blown by a teacher in the school playground. We all line up then go into school. When we get into school we find something to do then our teacher takes the register.We do either english or maths till half-past ten when it is break. We come back in at five to eleven and swap over work.At twelve o'clock we have lunch and a break.When we come in we do topic or sewing we go home at half past three.At seven p.m. I go to Guides then I go to bed.
